{
  "texts": [
    "Building upon this foundation, we extend the scalability and costeffectiveness of KEEPER by incorporating large-language models (LLMs), to adjudicate cases based on KEEPER's output.",
    "LLMs, recognized for their potential applications in the medical domain [4] [5] [6], offer a promising avenue for automating the adjudication process.",
    "Given privacy constraints, we evaluate in-house hosted LLMs-specifically, the commercially available GPT-3.5 Turbo and GPT-4, and the freely available Llama-2 and Sheep-Duck-Llama-2.",
    "To illustration our approach: one of the diseases evaluated in our study is osteoporosis, defined conceptually (per Supplementary Table 3) as \"a skeletal disorder characterized by decreased bone density and strength, leading to fragile bones and an increased risk of fractures.\"",
    "Our phenotype algorithm identifies cases by the first recorded diagnosis code that maps to the standard concept of Osteoporosis or any of its descendants within the CDM, facilitating cross-system compatibility 7."
  ]
}